included.description: The winner of Red Dot Award - Design Concept in 2011. The design of mobile bluetooth earphone came from two-person team.
included.title: Red Dot Award

included.description:
Phantom is a startup which was recognized as one of the most creative companies in China by Fast Company in 2014.

Conceptualized key features for company's smart home product, leveraging the massive usage data to deliver a non-intrusive user experience. Created UI wireframes and paper prototypes of the feature on the mobile platform.

Conducted intensive user researches on the service process from purchasing, shipping, installing to setting up. Employed various research methods such as user interview, context inquiry and hallway testing based on specific research task. Re-designed multiple flows based on research findings.
included.title: Product Researcher & Designer

included.description:
Uncovered potential user needs for data-aware application features from researches conducted earlier. Conceptualized product ideas from the finding and created designs accordingly. Led a product team to drive the design into live product with 28,615 daily active users.

Created user research strategies and plans for various Baidu projects. Applied appropriate research methods based on specific project needs. Employed non-traditional tools/medium (Weibo diary etc.) as the research required. Regularly conducted user research activities such as user interviews, focus groups and usability tests.

Team MVP in Q2 2013 (8 people team).

Winner of the Server and Cloud Platform Innovative Product Award.
included.title: User Experience Researcher

included.description:
Employed a series of human-centered approaches such as exploratory research to learn users and uncover opportunities. Collaborated with product team to explore new concepts in design process, conceptualize new features by fast iteration in agile process, such as test the new feature with mockups and adjust features according to design criteria. 

Independently conducted research of product development, including scoped research process, analyzed and interpreted results, synthesized findings to design implications, drew storyboard, generated low-fi prototype. Utilized research methods such as in-depth interview, usability test, card sort and A/B Testing.
included.title: Design Research Intern

included.description:
Collaborated with other UX researchers and development teams to create competitive analysis and user profiles & scenarios for various early-stage products.

Designed user interface for Social Radio product which has been published through the online OVI store. Created and presented storyboards for various product concepts.
included.title: Product Design Intern

included.description: Led a team of 5 as a product manager to design a digital bookmark and social network to alleviate social isolation of LGBT seniors in Southeast Michigan. Publication submitted to 2015 CHI Conference - Student Design Competition.
included.title: SHAREMARK - CHI STUDENT DESIGN COMPETITION
